          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 64</h1><p><strong>Questions 15 - 16</strong></p><p>Choose <strong>TWO</strong> letters <strong>A</strong> - <strong>E</strong>.</p><p>According to the sales manager, which TWO things make these apartments special?</p><p>15</p><p>16</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong></th><th>They are environmentally friendly.</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong></td><td>The building is historical.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong></td><td>There are unique facilities.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>D</strong></td><td>They are very safe and secure.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>E</strong></td><td>The weather is very warm and sunny.</td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Questions 21 - 24</strong></p><p>Choose the correct letter <strong>A, B or C</strong>.</p><p>21 Why did James choose his work placement?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong></th><th>He didn’t get the position in the software company.</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong></td><td>He thought the products were the most interesting.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong></td><td>He really wanted to work for a global organisation.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>22 What did he like the most about his work placement?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong></th><th>The opportunity to analyze different markets</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong></td><td>The chance to experience many different departments.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong></td><td>Being able to learn new skills.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>23 What did he not like about working for the company?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong></th><th>Many people took risks with the money.</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong></td><td>He was always told what to do.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong></td><td>He didn’t have much of an effect on the business.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>24 What did he value most about the organisation of his training?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong></th><th>He worked with some really good managers.</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong></td><td>He never had any problems.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong></td><td>There was continuity throughout his experience.</td></tr></tbody></table>",
